# EMS Protocol App — Core Rules

## What this is
React Native + Expo Router app for paramedics. Visual decision-tree flowcharts replace paragraph-form EMS protocols. Source: Central Arizona Red Book 2026.

## Tech stack
- React Native, Expo SDK 54, Expo Router
- react-native-svg (flowcharts)
- react-native-gesture-handler + react-native-reanimated (pinch zoom)
- Supabase (backend)
- Anthropic Claude API (Scenario AI feature)

## Communication
- Direct, no hand-holding, no excessive disclaimers
- Concrete file paths and exact commands — Kyle is not a developer
- Call out bad ideas explicitly — don't write polite workarounds
- Don't re-suggest tunnel mode for Expo. LAN mode only.
- Use Command Prompt, not PowerShell
- Tests live on Samsung Note 10+ via Expo Go

## CRITICAL — Three-file rule for new protocols
Adding any new protocol REQUIRES editing three files in the same response:
1. CREATE `components/protocols/[Name]Flowchart.tsx`
2. EDIT `app/protocol/[id].tsx` — add import + PROTOCOL_META entry + ternary case
3. EDIT `app/(tabs)/protocols.tsx` — add to PROTOCOLS array (and CATEGORIES if new)

Skipping #3 = protocol won't appear in list.
Skipping #2 = route won't render the new component.

## Master template
`components/protocols/SeizureFlowchart.tsx` is the v2 master template.
ALL new flowcharts copy its architecture exactly. Do NOT reconstruct from description.
When generating a new flowchart, read SeizureFlowchart.tsx first, then copy its structure.